<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-03-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-03-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="55" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d55">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 23700/7.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Beaupré</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">The
                                        Hague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-03-31"><hi rend="italic">March 31,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Beaupré says he is notified by the Luxemburg Government of the arrest
                            made in compliance with the telegraphic request of Wood, detective
                            captain, of Chicago, at Luxemburg on March 24 of Nicholas Knepper on
                            charge of larceny. Asks if extradition papers are being sent t-o the
                            legation.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>